-- Xylem Acquires U.K. Wastewater Services Company for $57 Million
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-02-05T17:32:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-05/xylem-acquires-u-k-wastewater-services-company-for-57-million.html
Xylem Inc. (XYL) , the ITT Corp. spinoff
that specializes in water technologies, said today that it
acquired Pims Group, a U.K. wastewater services company, in a
$57 million deal.  Pims, based in Farnborough, helps design, install and
maintain pumping systems, sewers, oil interceptors, drains and
sewage-treatment plants, White Plains, New York-based Xylem said
in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
